Input Validation (C#)
Question:
Fill in the blank to write a C# function that checks if a user input string contains only alphanumeric characters (letters and numbers). If not, throw an exception.

csharp

public void ValidateUserInput(string userInput)
{
    if (!Regex.IsMatch(userInput, @"^[__________]*$"))  // Fill in the blank
    {
        throw new ArgumentException("Invalid input. Only alphanumeric characters are allowed.");
    }
}
